caption.text:
ODHA (Orang Dengan HIV AIDS) is a person who got infected by human
immunodeficiency virus. This virus is a blood-borne virus which is transmitted via sexual intercourse, shared intravenous drug, and mother-to-child transmission.
This virus will not be transmitted just by touching the ODHA.
So, WE should remove the stigma about discriminating people with HIV/AIDS and give them our love and empathy, not discrimination and Today, 1st of December is World HIV/AIDS day.

I, Michelle Lavinia Lee, proud of joining all Ambassador of Public Health of AMSA-Indonesia to share this fact.

So come and join us to commemorate this day. Spread the facts!

#OneHugWontHurt
#AMSAIndonesia #ReThinkHIV
